results.abstract: Is launched with cosmonauts Lt Col Vyacheslav Zudov and Lt Col Valery Rozhdesvensky; cosmonauts to continue research and experiments begun by Soyuz 21; to board Salyut 5 space station (M)

headline.main: 2 SOVIET ASTRONAUTS START TRIP TO SALYUT; Some Believe Soyuz Mission May Try to Break U.S. Record of 84 Days in Space Station

results.snippet: MOSCOW, Oct. 14 The Soviet Union today launched a new Soyuz spacecraft carrying two astronauts for a planned rendezvous with a space station that has been orbiting the earth since June.

byline.original: By CHRISTOPHER S. WREN Special to The New York Times
